com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document

Class SpenPageDoc

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenPageDoc

  • public final class SpenPageDoc
extends Object
    Page document Class
    This class contains all the data in a page. It manages the objects in the page and provides the command history for undo and redo commands.
    Since:
    3.0.0

      ArrayList<SpenObjectBase> findObjectInClosedCurve(int typeFilter, PointF[] points)
      Find the objects of the specified type contained in the closed curves defined by the specified points.
      The points connect the curve in order.
      If the curve does not intersect, this method connects the first point and the last point.
      If two points overlap, one of them is ignored and the next point is connected.
      Objects within object containers cannot be found.

      boolean isRedoable()
      Check if the action is redoable.
      Check if the redo stack in the history manager is empty.
      If it is empty, there is no command to redo, and the method returns false.
      If it is not empty, it returns true.
      Always use this method before calling page.redo().
      boolean isRedoable(int userId)
      Check if the action is redoable for the specified user.
      Check if the redo stack in the history manager for this user is empty.
      If it is empty, there is no command to redo, and the method returns false.
      If it is not empty, it returns true.
      Always use this method before calling page.redo().
      boolean isUndoable()
      Check if the action is undoable.
      Check if the undo stack in the history manager is empty.
      If it is empty, there is no command to undo, and this method returns false.
      If it is not empty, it returns true.
      Always call this method before calling page.undo().
      boolean isUndoable(int userId)
      Check if the action is undoable for the specified user.
      Check if the undo stack in the history manager for this user is empty.

      If it is not empty, it returns true.
      Always use this method before calling page.undo().

      Undo the command for the specified user and return the previous state information for updating the canvas.
      After undo, the canvas view needs to be updated.
      SpenPageDoc.HistoryUpdateInfo[] undoAll()
      Undo all the commands in the undo stack of the history manager and return the previous state information for updating the canvas.
      After undoAll, the canvas view needs to be updated.
      SpenPageDoc.HistoryUpdateInfo[] undoAll(int userId)
      Undo all the commands for the specified user in the undo stack of the history manager and return the previous state information for updating the canvas.
      After undoAll, the canvas view needs to be updated.
      SpenPageDoc.HistoryUpdateInfo[] undoToTag()
      Undo the command to the tag and return the previous state information for updating the canvas.
      After undoToTag, the redo stack is cleared and the canvas view needs to be updated.
      Note: If history tag out of the undo stack, it will be removed.
      void unloadObject()
      Unload the objects in the page which is not being attached to view.
      This method saves the objects and layers on the page in the cache directory and unloads them from memory.
      The unloaded objects cannot be used any more.
      When objects are unloaded, the methods for the objects trigger the loadObject method internally.
      You cannot use methods that receive an unloaded object instance as their parameter.
      The command history stack for the unloaded objects is cleared.

      • findObjectInClosedCurve

        public ArrayList<SpenObjectBase> findObjectInClosedCurve(int typeFilter,
                                                         PointF[] points)
        Find the objects of the specified type contained in the closed curves defined by the specified points.
        The points connect the curve in order.
        If the curve does not intersect, this method connects the first point and the last point.
        If two points overlap, one of them is ignored and the next point is connected.
        Objects within object containers cannot be found.
        Parameters:
        typeFilter - The object filter.
        For example:
        findObjectInClosedCurve(PageDoc.FIND_TYPE_STROKE, points)
        The valid values are:
        FIND_TYPE_STROKE
        FIND_TYPE_ALL
        points - The point array that defines the curves.
        Returns:
        The object list
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the arguments passed are invalid.
        Since:
        3.0.0

      • loadObject

        public void loadObject()
                throws IOException
        Load all objects.
        When a page is first created, the isObjectLoaded() method returns true, but if you create a NoteDoc with an SPD file and get a page, the isObjectLoaded() method returns false.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the page is not attached to a note or if the isObjectLoaded() returns true exception is thrown.
        IOException - Thrown if the page file is not found.
        Since:
        3.0.0
        See Also:
        isObjectLoaded(), unloadObject()

      • unloadObject

        public void unloadObject()
                  throws IOException
        Unload the objects in the page which is not being attached to view.
        This method saves the objects and layers on the page in the cache directory and unloads them from memory.
        The unloaded objects cannot be used any more.
        When objects are unloaded, the methods for the objects trigger the loadObject method internally.
        You cannot use methods that receive an unloaded object instance as their parameter.
        The command history stack for the unloaded objects is cleared.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the page is not attached to a note.
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the isObjectLoaded() method returns false.
        IOException - Thrown if the page file is not found.
        Since:
        3.0.0
        See Also:
        isObjectLoaded(), loadObject()

      • copy

        public void copy(SpenPageDoc sourcePage)
        Copy the objects from the specified page document.
        After copy, the history stack is cleared.
        The objects on the pasted page are resized on the target page. If the width of the pasted page is 720 and that of the target page is 1080, all the objects including rect, point, margin, line spacing, border width, font size and pen size are resized by 150%.
        Parameters:
        sourcePage - The source page.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the orientation of the source page is not the same as the orientation of the target page.
        Since:
        3.0.0

      • isUndoable

        public boolean isUndoable()
        Check if the action is undoable.
        Check if the undo stack in the history manager is empty.
        If it is empty, there is no command to undo, and this method returns false.
        If it is not empty, it returns true.
        Always call this method before calling page.undo(). 
         if (page.isUndoable() == true) {
 spenSurfaceView.updateUndo(page.undo());
 }
        Returns:
        true if the undo stack is not empty.
        false if the undo stack is empty.
        Since:
        3.0.0
        See Also:
        undo()

      • isRedoable

        If it is not empty, it returns true.

         if (page.isRedoable() == true) {
 spenSurfaceView.updateRedo(page.redo());
 }

        true if the redo stack is not empty.
        false if the redo stack is empty.

      • setUndoLimit

        public void setUndoLimit(int undoLimit)
        Set the limit for the number of undo commands in the undo stack. The default value is 50.
        The 51st command pushes, the first command out of the undo stack of the history manager if the limit is set to 50.
        Use this method to change the limit. 
         page.setUndoLimit(100);
        Parameters:
        undoLimit - The undo command limit.
        Since:
        3.0.0

      • setHistoryManagerMode

        public void setHistoryManagerMode(int mode)
        Set the specified mode for the history manager.
        SpenPageDoc supports multi mode (SpenMultiView) and single mode (SpenView, SpenSurfaceView).

        In the multiple view mode, Not supported full API set of PageDoc. We guarantee only the API set of SPenObjectBase and its children and the appendObject and removeObject API of PageDoc. Because in the multiple view mode, the history data is classified by object's API set. So the APIs of PageDoc that handle more than one object dose not work properly.
        Parameters:
        mode - The history manager mode.
        The valid values are:
        HISTORY_MANAGER_MODE_SINGLE_VIEW
        HISTORY_MANAGER_MODE_MULTIPLE_VIEW
        Since:
        3.0.0
        See Also:
        getHistoryManagerMode()

      • setDefaultSaveOption

        public static void setDefaultSaveOption(boolean compatibleMode)
        Set the default save option for all page in the note

        S Pen SDK 4.0 has a big change. The ObjectShape is supported since version 4.0. And, the ObjectImage and ObjectTextbox have some internal changes. So, some data for S Pen SDK 4.0 will not work properly in S Pen SDK 3.x.
        If you save the note data with compatibleMode, the output file will work for S Pen SDK 3.x. But, the ObjectShape saves as an ObjectImage and some data will be changed and lost to support S Pen SDK 3.x. And, of course, this process makes some latency and overhead.
        If you save the note data without compatibleMode, the output file can not work for S Pen SDK 3.x properly. It doesn't mean that the output data never work for S Pen SDK 3.x. It depend on the internal data of this NoteDoc instance. For example, if this NoteDoc has ObjectStrokes only, the output file will work properly for S Pen SDK 3.x.
        Parameters:
        compatibleMode - Set to true to save this page for which is compatible with S Pen SDK 3.x, set to false to save this page for which is used for S Pen SDK 4.0 or later.
        Since:
        4.0.0
